[{"id":"VR860304","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">If the incident angle <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"theta sub i\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"theta sub i\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>θ</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></math></span></span> is varied, which of the following graphs could correctly show <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the sine of theta sub r\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"the sine of theta sub r\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>sin</mi><mo>⁡</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mi>r</mi></msub></math></span></span> as a function of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the sine of theta sub i\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"the sine of theta sub i\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>sin</mi><mo>⁡</mo><msub><mi>θ</mi><mi>i</mi></msub></math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR860304_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A beam of light in Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> with index of refraction <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n sub 1\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"n sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <msub> <mi>n</mi> <mn>1</mn> </msub> </math></span></span> is incident on the boundary with Material <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> with index of refraction <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n sub 2\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"n sub 2\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math></span></span>, where <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n sub 2 is greater than n sub 1\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"n sub 2 is greater than n sub 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math></span></span>. The incident angle of the beam wi